          content: [{
            title: "Topic 1 - Knocking it Out of the Park",
            audioLinkSlow: "assets/audio/LESSON 10 - WORK PLACE/Recording 10.1 - Slow Speech - Topic 1 - Knocking it Out of the Park.mp3",
            audioLinkNative: "assets/audio/LESSON 10 - WORK PLACE/Recording 10.2 - Native Speech - Topic 1 - Knocking It Out of the Park.mp3",
            data: "<div><p>Maya and Colin have to give an important marketing <strong>presentation</strong>. However, they haven\u2019t finished it yet.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>Maya v\xE0 Colin ph\u1EA3i th\u1EF1c hi\u1EC7n m\u1ED9t<strong> b\xE0i thuy\u1EBFt tr\xECnh</strong> ti\u1EBFp th\u1ECB quan tr\u1ECDng. Tuy nhi\xEAn, h\u1ECD v\u1EABn ch\u01B0a ho\xE0n th\xE0nh n\xF3.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> Hey Colin, do you want to finish our marketing presentation this afternoon?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> N\xE0y Colin, anh c\xF3 mu\u1ED1n ho\xE0n th\xE0nh b\xE0i thuy\u1EBFt tr\xECnh ti\u1EBFp th\u1ECB c\u1EE7a ch\xFAng ta trong chi\u1EC1u nay kh\xF4ng?</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> <strong>That\u2019s a good idea</strong>. Actually, <strong>are you free to talk about it now?</strong><br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> <strong>\u0110\xF3 l\xE0 m\u1ED9t \xFD hay</strong>. Th\u1EF1c ra, <strong>b\xE2y gi\u1EDD ch\u1ECB c\xF3 r\u1EA3nh \u0111\u1EC3 n\xF3i v\u1EC1 n\xF3 kh\xF4ng?</strong></em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> Sure. <strong>I\u2019m really worried about</strong> it.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> Ch\u1EAFc ch\u1EAFn r\u1ED3i. <strong>T\xF4i th\u1EF1c s\u1EF1 lo l\u1EAFng v\u1EC1 chuy\u1EC7n n\xE0y.</strong></em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> <strong>We\u2019ll be fine</strong>. Everyone is <strong>interested</strong> in what we have to say.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> <strong>Ch\xFAng ta s\u1EBD \u1ED5n th\xF4i</strong>. M\u1ECDi ng\u01B0\u1EDDi \u0111\u1EC1u <strong>quan t\xE2m</strong> t\u1EDBi nh\u1EEFng g\xEC ch\xFAng ta n\xF3i.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> <strong>That\u2019s a good point</strong>. But can I ask you one thing?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> <strong>\u0110\xF3 l\xE0 m\u1ED9t \u0111i\u1EC3m t\u1ED1t</strong>. Nh\u01B0ng t\xF4i c\xF3 th\u1EC3 h\u1ECFi anh m\u1ED9t \u0111i\u1EC1u kh\xF4ng?</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> <strong>Go ahead!</strong><br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin: C\u1EE9 h\u1ECFi \u0111i!</strong></em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> What is our marketing plan again?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> K\u1EBF ho\u1EA1ch ti\u1EBFp th\u1ECB c\u1EE7a ch\xFAng ta l\xE0 g\xEC nh\u1EC9?</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> What? I\u2019m <strong>confused</strong>. I thought you knew.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> C\xE1i g\xEC? T\xF4i <strong>b\u1ED1i r\u1ED1i</strong> \u0111\u1EA5y. T\xF4i ngh\u0129 l\xE0 ch\u1ECB bi\u1EBFt.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> I\u2019m confused, too, because I thought you knew. Oh no.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> T\xF4i c\u0169ng b\u1ED1i r\u1ED1i, v\xEC t\xF4i ngh\u0129 anh bi\u1EBFt. \u1ED2 kh\xF4ng.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> Okay. Don\u2019t panic. We\u2019re <strong>going to be</strong> fine.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> Ok. \u0110\u1EEBng ho\u1EA3ng s\u1EE3. Ch\xFAng ta <strong>s\u1EBD</strong> \u1ED5n th\xF4i.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> I\u2019m <strong>panicking</strong> a little bit. We need to make a <strong>polished</strong> and <strong>exciting</strong> marketing plan in\u2026 one day.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> T\xF4i h\u01A1i <strong>ho\u1EA3ng s\u1EE3</strong> m\u1ED9t ch\xFAt. Ch\xFAng ta c\u1EA7n ph\u1EA3i l\xE0m ra m\u1ED9t k\u1EBF ho\u1EA1ch ti\u1EBFp th\u1ECB<strong> trau chu\u1ED1t</strong> v\xE0 <strong>th\xFA v\u1ECB</strong> trong v\xF2ng\u2026 m\u1ED9t ng\xE0y.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> And we need to make a <strong>thrilling</strong> presentation. If our presentation is <strong>boring</strong>, we\u2019re going to get fired.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> C\xF2n v\u1EC1 ph\u1EA7n thuy\u1EBFt tr\xECnh, ch\xFAng ta c\u1EA7n l\xE0m cho b\xE0i thuy\u1EBFt tr\xECnh <strong>h\u1EA5p d\u1EABn</strong>. N\u1EBFu ph\u1EA7n tr\xECnh b\xE0y <strong>nh\xE0m ch\xE1n</strong>, ch\xFAng ta s\u1EBD b\u1ECB sa th\u1EA3i.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> That\u2019s so true\u2026 Oh no, here comes the boss!<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> \u0110\xF3 l\xE0 s\u1EF1 th\u1EADt\u2026 \xD4i kh\xF4ng, s\u1EBFp \u0111ang \u0111\u1EBFn!</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> Look <strong>relaxed</strong>!<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> Tr\xF4ng th\u1EADt <strong>tho\u1EA3i m\xE1i</strong> v\xE0o!</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> I can\u2019t look relaxed when I feel so <strong>stressed</strong>!<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> T\xF4i kh\xF4ng th\u1EC3 t\u1ECF ra tho\u1EA3i m\xE1i khi t\xF4i \u0111ang r\u1EA5t <strong>c\u0103ng th\u1EB3ng</strong>!</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Boss:</strong> Hi you two, I\u2019m looking forward to seeing your presentation!<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Boss:</strong> Ch\xE0o hai ng\u01B0\u1EDDi, t\xF4i r\u1EA5t tr\xF4ng \u0111\u1EE3i v\xE0o ph\u1EA7n tr\xECnh b\xE0y c\u1EE7a hai ng\u01B0\u1EDDi \u0111\u1EA5y!</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> Uh huh.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> V\xE2ng.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Boss:</strong> Do you need any <strong>support</strong> from IT?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Boss:</strong> Hai ng\u01B0\u1EDDi c\xF3 c\u1EA7n b\u1EA5t c\u1EE9 <strong>s\u1EF1 h\u1ED7 tr\u1EE3</strong> n\xE0o v\u1EC1 c\xF4ng ngh\u1EC7 kh\xF4ng?</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Maya:</strong> Nope, we\u2019re <strong>all set</strong>.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Maya:</strong> Kh\xF4ng, ch\xFAng t\xF4i<strong> t\u1EA5t c\u1EA3 \u0111\u1EC1u \u0111\xE3 s\u1EB5n s\xE0ng</strong>.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Boss:</strong> Great to hear. I think our entire quarter <strong>comes down to</strong> your marketing plan, and everyone<strong> feels the same way</strong>. I hope you guys<strong> knock it out of the park</strong> this afternoon.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Boss:</strong> Tuy\u1EC7t l\u1EAFm. T\xF4i ngh\u0129 r\u1EB1ng c\u1EA3 qu\xFD c\u1EE7a ch\xFAng ta<strong> tr\xF4ng \u0111\u1EE3i v\xE0o</strong> k\u1EBF ho\u1EA1ch ti\u1EBFp th\u1ECB c\u1EE7a hai ng\u01B0\u1EDDi, v\xE0 t\u1EA5t c\u1EA3 m\u1ECDi ng\u01B0\u1EDDi <strong>\u0111\u1EC1u c\u1EA3m th\u1EA5y nh\u01B0 v\u1EADy</strong>. T\xF4i hy v\u1ECDng hai ng\u01B0\u1EDDi s\u1EBD<strong> th\u1EC3 hi\u1EC7n th\u1EADt xu\u1EA5t s\u1EAFc</strong> bu\u1ED5i chi\u1EC1u nay.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> This afternoon?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> Chi\u1EC1u nay sao?</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Boss:</strong> Oh, we decided to move it up a bit.<strong> I</strong> <strong>hope you don\u2019t mind</strong>.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Boss:</strong> \xC0,ch\xFAng t\xF4i quy\u1EBFt \u0111\u1ECBnh chuy\u1EC3n l\u1ECBch l\xEAn m\u1ED9t ch\xFAt. <strong>T\xF4i hy v\u1ECDng hai ng\u01B0\u1EDDi kh\xF4ng phi\u1EC1n</strong>.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>Colin:</strong> Nope. No problem at all\u2026<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>Colin:</strong> Kh\xF4ng. Kh\xF4ng c\xF3 v\u1EA5n \u0111\u1EC1 g\xEC\u2026</em></span></p>\n              </div>"
          }, {
            title: "Topic 2 - Not \u201CManagement Material\u201D",
            audioLinkSlow: "assets/audio/LESSON 10 - WORK PLACE/Recording 10.3 - Slow Speech - Topic 2 - Not \u201CManagement Material\u201D.mp3",
            audioLinkNative: "assets/audio/LESSON 10 - WORK PLACE/Recording 10.4 - Native Speech - Topic 2 - Not Management Material.mp3",
            data: "<div><p>\u201CYou son, are an idiot!\u201D Said the <strong>manager</strong> to the \u2018<strong>managee</strong>.\u2019 \u201CYou\u2019re fired!\u201D<br>\n              \u201CAnd you Sir, are an idiom!\u201D Said the \u2018managee.\u2019 \u201CYou can\u2019t fire me, I quit!\u201D<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>\u201CCon trai, c\u1EADu l\xE0 \u0111\u1ED3 ng\u1ED1c!\u201D <strong>Ng\u01B0\u1EDDi qu\u1EA3n l\xFD</strong> n\xF3i v\u1EDBi \u201C<strong>ng\u01B0\u1EDDi b\u1ECB qu\u1EA3n l\xFD</strong>\u201D.\u2019 \u201CAnh b\u1ECB sa th\u1EA3i!\u201D</em></span><br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>\u201CV\xE0 th\u01B0a \xF4ng, \xF4ng c\u0169ng l\xE0 \u0111\u1ED3 ng\u1ED1c!\u201D \u201CNg\u01B0\u1EDDi b\u1ECB qu\u1EA3n l\xFD\u201D n\xF3i.\u2019 \u201C\xD4ng kh\xF4ng th\u1EC3 sa th\u1EA3i t\xF4i, t\xF4i b\u1ECF vi\u1EC7c!\u201D</em></span></p>\n              <p>If only we could all be as <strong>quick-witted</strong> as Steve Martin\u2019s Clouseau in the Pink Panther, when it comes to our managers at work.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>Gi\xE1 nh\u01B0 t\u1EA5t c\u1EA3 ch\xFAng ta \u0111\u1EC1u c\xF3 th\u1EC3 <strong>nhanh tr\xED</strong> nh\u01B0 nh\xE2n v\u1EADt Clouseau c\u1EE7a Steve Martin trong ho\u1EA1t h\xECnh Pink Panther, khi nh\u1EAFc \u0111\u1EBFn nh\u1EEFng ng\u01B0\u1EDDi qu\u1EA3n l\xFD c\u1EE7a ch\xFAng ta \u1EDF n\u01A1i l\xE0m vi\u1EC7c.</em></span></p>\n              <p>I have no doubt that being a manager is a tough job. It\u2019s a balancing act. How does a leader <strong>motivate</strong> employees to do their work best and still maintain professional boundaries and mutual respect? For example, my new manager is a nice guy, but instead of allowing me the time and space I need to do my job, he\u2019s constantly in my face, trying to <strong>micromanage</strong> everything I do. To be honest, I\u2019d like to smash him in the face with a frying pan. But all I have is a lousy <strong>stapler</strong> on my desk so I\u2019m trying to figure out how I can staple his mouth shut before he comes back to hover again.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>T\xF4i ch\u1EAFc ch\u1EAFn qu\u1EA3n l\xFD l\xE0 m\u1ED9t c\xF4ng vi\u1EC7c kh\xF3 kh\u0103n. \u0110\xF3 l\xE0 m\u1ED9t c\xF4ng vi\u1EC7c c\xE2n b\u1EB1ng. L\xE0m th\u1EBF n\xE0o m\u1ED9t nh\xE0 l\xE3nh \u0111\u1EA1o <strong>th\xFAc \u0111\u1EA9y</strong> nh\xE2n vi\xEAn l\xE0m vi\u1EC7c t\u1ED1t nh\u1EA5t m\xE0 v\u1EABn duy tr\xEC s\u1EF1 chuy\xEAn nghi\u1EC7p v\xE0 t\xF4n tr\u1ECDng l\u1EABn nhau? V\xED d\u1EE5, ng\u01B0\u1EDDi qu\u1EA3n l\xFD m\u1EDBi c\u1EE7a t\xF4i l\xE0 m\u1ED9t ng\u01B0\u1EDDi t\u1ED1t, nh\u01B0ng thay v\xEC cho t\xF4i th\u1EDDi gian v\xE0 kh\xF4ng gian \u0111\u1EC3 l\xE0m c\xF4ng vi\u1EC7c c\u1EE7a t\xF4i, \xF4ng ta li\xEAn t\u1EE5c \u1EDF tr\u01B0\u1EDBc m\u1EB7t t\xF4i, c\u1ED1 g\u1EAFng <strong>ki\u1EC3m so\xE1t t\u1EEBng chi ti\u1EBFt nh\u1ECF</strong> t\u1EA5t c\u1EA3 m\u1ECDi th\u1EE9. N\xF3i th\u1EADt, t\xF4i mu\u1ED1n \u0111\u1EADp v\xE0o m\u1EB7t \xF4ng ta b\u1EB1ng m\u1ED9t c\xE1i ch\u1EA3o, nh\u01B0ng t\xF4i ch\u1EC9 c\xF3 c\xE1i d\u1EADp ghim r\u1EDFm tr\xEAn b\xE0n l\xE0m vi\u1EC7c, v\xEC v\u1EADy t\xF4i \u0111ang c\u1ED1 g\u1EAFng t\xECm c\xE1ch l\xE0m th\u1EBF n\xE0o \u0111\u1EC3 c\xF3 th\u1EC3 <strong>d\u1EADp ghim</strong> c\xE1i mi\u1EC7ng c\u1EE7a \xF4ng ta l\u1EA1i tr\u01B0\u1EDBc khi \xF4ng ta l\u1EA1i l\u01B0\u1EE3n l\u1EDD l\u1EA7n n\u1EEFa.</em></span></p>\n              <p>I know he\u2019s <strong>under a lot of pressure</strong>. He has to <strong>report</strong> to his boss, the same way I have to report to him\u2026 but he got up and started grilling me about a report that wasn\u2019t even due for three weeks. I couldn\u2019t believe it. My head started spinning and I\u2019m pretty sure my eyes were bulging out of my head too.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>T\xF4i bi\u1EBFt \xF4ng \u1EA5y \u0111ang<strong> ch\u1ECBu r\u1EA5t nhi\u1EC1u \xE1p l\u1EF1c</strong>. \xD4ng \u1EA5y ph\u1EA3i <strong>b\xE1o c\xE1o</strong> v\u1EDBi s\u1EBFp c\u1EE7a m\xECnh, theo c\xF9ng m\u1ED9t c\xE1ch t\xF4i ph\u1EA3i b\xE1o c\xE1o v\u1EDBi \xF4ng ta\u2026 nh\u01B0ng \xF4ng \u1EA5y \u0111\xE3 \u0111\u1EE9ng d\u1EADy v\xE0 b\u1EAFt \u0111\u1EA7u tra t\u1EA5n t\xF4i v\u1EC1 c\xE1i b\xE1o c\xE1o ch\u01B0a \u0111\u1EBFn h\u1EA1n trong ba tu\u1EA7n n\u1EEFa. T\xF4i kh\xF4ng th\u1EC3 tin \u0111\u01B0\u1EE3c. \u0110\u1EA7u t\xF4i b\u1EAFt \u0111\u1EA7u quay cu\u1ED3ng v\xE0 t\xF4i kh\xE1 ch\u1EAFc ch\u1EAFn r\u1EB1ng m\u1EAFt t\xF4i c\u0169ng mu\u1ED1n nh\u1EA3y ra kh\u1ECFi \u0111\u1EA7u c\u1EE7a t\xF4i qu\xE1.</em></span></p>\n              <p><strong>I\u2019ve never really thought about this before</strong>, but I know I need to make some <strong>sacrifices</strong> if I want to<strong> move up in the world</strong>. <strong>There\u2019s no doubt</strong> in my mind that I can, or that I will. But one thing I <strong>know for sure</strong> is when I do? I want to be a friend to my colleagues, not a <strong>bossy</strong> one either. I really feel bad for the guy\u2019s dog.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em><strong>T\xF4i ch\u01B0a bao gi\u1EDD th\u1EF1c s\u1EF1 ngh\u0129 v\u1EC1 \u0111i\u1EC1u n\xE0y tr\u01B0\u1EDBc \u0111\xE2y</strong>, nh\u01B0ng t\xF4i bi\u1EBFt t\xF4i c\u1EA7n ph\u1EA3i <strong>hy sinh</strong> m\u1ED9t ch\xFAt n\u1EBFu t\xF4i mu\u1ED1n <strong>th\u0103ng ti\u1EBFn trong th\u1EBF gi\u1EDBi n\xE0y</strong>. Trong t\xE2m tr\xED t\xF4i <strong>kh\xF4ng nghi ng\u1EDD g\xEC</strong> l\xE0 t\xF4i c\xF3 th\u1EC3, t\xF4i s\u1EBD l\xE0m \u0111\u01B0\u1EE3c, nh\u01B0ng m\u1ED9t \u0111i\u1EC1u t\xF4i <strong>bi\u1EBFt ch\u1EAFc ch\u1EAFn</strong> l\xE0 khi t\xF4i l\xE0m \u0111\u01B0\u1EE3c, l\xE0 g\xEC? T\xF4i mu\u1ED1n l\xE0 m\u1ED9t ng\u01B0\u1EDDi b\u1EA1n v\u1EDBi \u0111\u1ED3ng nghi\u1EC7p c\u1EE7a t\xF4i, kh\xF4ng ph\u1EA3i l\xE0 m\u1ED9t ng\u01B0\u1EDDi b\u1EA1n <strong>h\xE1ch d\u1ECBch.</strong> T\xF4i th\u1EF1c s\u1EF1 c\u1EA3m th\u1EA5y t\u1ED9i cho con ch\xF3 c\u1EE7a \xF4ng ta.</em></span></p>\n              <p><span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>You son, are an idiot! \u2013 And you Sir, are an idiom!\u201D</em></span><br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>+ \u0110\xE2y l\xE0 c\xE1ch ch\u01A1i ch\u1EEF c\u1EE7a ng\u01B0\u1EDDi vi\u1EBFt! C\u1EA3 2 t\u1EEB \u201CIdiom\u201D v\xE0 \u201CIdiot\u201D \u0111\u1EC1u c\xF3 g\u1ED1c t\u1EEB: Idios.</em></span><br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>+ \u1EDE \u0111\xE2y \xF4ng nh\xE2n vi\xEAn kh\xF4ng d\xE1m ch\u1EEDi m\u1EAFng th\u1EB3ng \xF4ng s\u1EBFp l\xE0 \u201C\u0111\u1ED3 ng\u1ED1c\u201D n\xEAn \u0111\xE3 n\xF3i l\xE1i \u0111i!</em></span></p>\n              </div>"
          }, {
            title: "Topic 3 - Office Gossip, It_s Not All Bad",
            audioLinkSlow: "assets/audio/LESSON 10 - WORK PLACE/Recording 10.5 - Slow Speech -Topic 3 - Office Gossip, It_s Not All Bad.mp3",
            audioLinkNative: "assets/audio/LESSON 10 - WORK PLACE/Recording 10.6 - Native Speech - Topic 3 - Office Gossip It_s Not All Bad.mp3",
            data: "<div><p>Is it <strong>gossip</strong>, or <strong>authentic assessment</strong>?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>C\xF3 ph\u1EA3i \u0111\xF3 l\xE0<strong> th\u1ECB phi</strong>, hay s\u1EF1 <strong>\u0111\xE1nh gi\xE1 ch\xE2n th\u1EF1c</strong>?</em></span></p>\n              <p>It\u2019s true, no one likes a gossiper, but research shows that the <strong>rumor mill</strong> is a good place for passing out information, especially if the rumor mill is your place of work. \u201CInformal communication\u201D that can help spread information more quickly than formal channels of communications, like company e-mails or staff meetings, can be beneficial.<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>\u0110\xF3 l\xE0 s\u1EF1 th\u1EADt, kh\xF4ng ai th\xEDch m\u1ED9t ng\u01B0\u1EDDi \u0111\u01B0a chuy\u1EC7n, nh\u01B0ng nghi\xEAn c\u1EE9u cho th\u1EA5y r\u1EB1ng <strong>ph\u1EA1m vi tin \u0111\u1ED3n</strong> l\xE0 m\u1ED9t n\u01A1i t\u1ED1t \u0111\u1EC3 truy\u1EC1n th\xF4ng tin, \u0111\u1EB7c bi\u1EC7t n\u1EBFu ph\u1EA1m vi tin \u0111\u1ED3n l\xE0 \u1EDF n\u01A1i l\xE0m vi\u1EC7c c\u1EE7a b\u1EA1n. \u201CGiao ti\u1EBFp kh\xF4ng ch\xEDnh th\u1EE9c\u201D c\xF3 th\u1EC3 gi\xFAp lan truy\u1EC1n th\xF4ng tin nhanh h\u01A1n so v\u1EDBi c\xE1c k\xEAnh truy\u1EC1n th\xF4ng ch\xEDnh th\u1EE9c, nh\u01B0 e-mails c\xF4ng ty ho\u1EB7c c\xE1c cu\u1ED9c h\u1ECDp nh\xE2n vi\xEAn, n\xF3 c\xF3 th\u1EC3 c\xF3 l\u1EE3i.</em></span></p>\n              <p>I\u2019m sure everybody has experienced this first-hand: a manager makes an important announcement, only to find out that half the company already knew about it. More likely, many knew, even before he did!<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>T\xF4i ch\u1EAFc r\u1EB1ng t\u1EA5t c\u1EA3 m\u1ECDi ng\u01B0\u1EDDi \u0111\xE3 tr\u1EA3i qua chuy\u1EC7n n\xE0y: m\u1ED9t ng\u01B0\u1EDDi qu\u1EA3n l\xFD \u0111\u01B0a ra th\xF4ng b\xE1o quan tr\u1ECDng, ch\u1EC9 \u0111\u1EC3 bi\u1EBFt r\u1EB1ng m\u1ED9t n\u1EEDa c\xF4ng ty \u0111\xE3 bi\u1EBFt v\u1EC1 n\xF3. Kh\u1EA3 n\u0103ng l\xE0 \u0111\xE3 c\xF3 nhi\u1EC1u ng\u01B0\u1EDDi bi\u1EBFt, th\u1EADm ch\xED tr\u01B0\u1EDBc c\u1EA3 \xF4ng \u1EA5y!</em></span></p>\n              <p>While gossip is <strong>frustrating</strong> and <strong>fraught</strong> with <strong>negative</strong> consequences, it\u2019s also a sign of what companies care about. So yes, pay attention, but ALWAYS consider your source. Ask yourself: What is the motivation behind the information being given? Is it just a <strong>disgruntled</strong> co-worker who\u2019s <strong>mean</strong>? Or, is the <strong>water cooler</strong> talk you\u2019re hearing, a <strong>legendary</strong> story that offers valuable <strong>insight</strong> for <strong>navigating</strong> your life?<br>\n              <span style=\"color:#7e8c8d\"><em>M\u1EB7c d\xF9 bu\xF4n chuy\u1EC7n<strong> g\xE2y kh\xF3 ch\u1ECBu</strong> v\xE0 <strong>\u0111\u1EA7y r\u1EABy</strong> nh\u1EEFng h\u1EADu qu\u1EA3 <strong>ti\xEAu c\u1EF1c</strong>, \u0111\xF3 c\u0169ng l\xE0 d\u1EA5u hi\u1EC7u c\u1EE7a \u0111i\u1EC1u m\xE0 c\xF4ng ty quan t\xE2m. V\xEC v\u1EADy, \u0111\xFAng, h\xE3y ch\xFA \xFD, nh\u01B0ng ph\u1EA3i lu\xF4n c\xE2n nh\u1EAFc ngu\u1ED3n c\u1EE7a b\u1EA1n. H\xE3y t\u1EF1 h\u1ECFi: \u0111\u1ED9ng l\u1EF1c \u0111\u1EB1ng sau c\xE1c th\xF4ng tin \u0111\u01B0\u1EE3c \u0111\u01B0a ra l\xE0 g\xEC? N\xF3 ch\u1EC9 l\xE0 m\u1ED9t \u0111\u1ED3ng nghi\u1EC7p <strong>b\u1EA5t b\xECnh</strong> \u0111ang tr\u1EDF n\xEAn<strong> h\u1EB9p h\xF2i</strong>? Hay l\xE0 c\xE2u <strong>chuy\u1EC7n phi\u1EBFm</strong> m\xE0 b\u1EA1n \u0111ang nghe, l\u1EA1i l\xE0 m\u1ED9t c\xE2u chuy\u1EC7n <strong>huy\u1EC1n tho\u1EA1i</strong> cho b\u1EA1n c\xE1i <strong>nh\xECn s\xE2u s\u1EAFc</strong> \u0111\xE1ng gi\xE1 \u0111\u1EC3<strong> \u0111\u1ECBnh h\u01B0\u1EDBng</strong> cu\u1ED9c s\u1ED1ng c\u1EE7a m\xECnh?</em></span></p>\n              </div>"
          }]
